        <label>Figure 6.</label>
        <caption>
          <p><italic>recombClust</italic> classification recovers the population structure detected by principal component analysis (PCA) of SNP data. In <italic>D. melanogaster</italic> inversions [In(2L)t, In(2R)NS, and In(3R)Mo], each point represents the first two principal components of an inbred line, colored by <italic>recombClust</italic> classification: (black) subpopulation 1; (red) subpopulation 2. In humans, each point represents the first two PCs of a diploid individual colored by the <italic>recombClust</italic> classification: (green) subpop1/subpop1; (blue) subpop1/subpop2; (cyan) subpop2/subpop2.</p>
